Inclusion Criteria: Diagnosis of ASD as defined by DSM-5, confirmed by clinical evaluation and supported by the Autism Diagnostic Observation Schedule (ADOS)
Inclusion Criteria: Age 18-35 years inclusive
Inclusion Criteria: IQ estimate of greater than or equal to 80
Inclusion Criteria: Clinical Global Impression - Severity scale of 4 (moderate) or greater
Inclusion Criteria: Existing allowed concomitant medication treatment stable for the 8 weeks prior to study entry, and no anticipated changes
Inclusion Criteria: Capacity to provide informed consent as demonstrated by a score of greater than 14.5 on the UBACC
Inclusion Criteria: Ability to comply with all protocol procedures and assessments
Inclusion Criteria: Availability of an informant willing to provide information regarding subject behavior and health status
Inclusion Criteria: Evidence of EEG biomarker deficit as defined in section C4.3
Exclusion Criteria: Evidence of current drug or alcohol abuse or dependence
Exclusion Criteria: History of current or prior drug or alcohol use or dependence in past 12 months
Exclusion Criteria: History of seizure disorder (except febrile seizures)
Exclusion Criteria: Clinically significant aggressive, disruptive, or suicidal behavior in the 3 months prior to study enrollment

Exclusion Criteria: Clinical evidence of lifetime history of psychotic disorder, bipolar disorder, or other serious psychopathology which in the judgment of the study physician would impair the individuals ability to comply with the protocol or potentially increase risk of adverse events

Exclusion Criteria: Presence of a chronic medical condition or prohibited medication (see list in Human Subjects section) which would potentially interfere with the assessment of treatment effects, or interact with study medications (eg. hepatic, neurologic, renal disease) to increase risk to the subject.
Exclusion Criteria: History of narrow-angle glaucoma
Exclusion Criteria: History of paradoxical reactions to benzodiazepines
Exclusion Criteria: Clinically significant deviation from the reference range in clinical laboratory test results at screening, as judged by the investigator
Exclusion Criteria: ALT or AST greater than the upper limit of the laboratory standard reference range at screening.
Exclusion Criteria: EKG abnormalities considered to be clinically significant as determined by the investigator and confirmed by an experienced cardiologist
Exclusion Criteria: Fredericia-corrected QT (QTcF) interval of >450 msec
Exclusion Criteria: Clinical judgment of the study physician of inability to perform the requirements of the study
Exclusion Criteria: For sexually active female and male subjects, refusal to agree to maintain a double-barrier birth control method during protocol participation

ElementDescription: Sequence Number
Notes:
The FSEQNO variable in the ADJ form has a special interpretation compared to other forms.
For example, ADJ FSEQNO of '1' can be thought of as being '001', FSEQNO of '2' can be thought of as
being '002', and FSEQNO of '3' can be thought of as being '003'.
The first digit of FSEQNO relates to the corresponding ENF sequence number at that visit and the third
digit relates to the specific adjudicator who completed the adjudication form.
